# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MARITIME AI ESTIMATOR — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your real keys.
# .env.local is gitignored — it will NEVER be committed to GitHub.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── REQUIRED ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GitHub Personal Access Token — used to access GitHub Models (free AI API)
#
# How to get it:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a name like "maritime-ai-estimator"
# 4. No special scopes needed — leave all checkboxes unchecked
# 5. Click "Generate token" and paste it here
#
# Why this works: GitHub Copilot Pro includes access to GitHub Models.
# GitHub Models provides GPT-4o-mini for free via an OpenAI-compatible API.
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here

# ── OPTIONAL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WeatherAPI.com API Key — for LIVE marine weather data
#
# Without this key, the app uses realistic Baltic Sea average values (still works fine).
# For the pitch demo, real data is impressive but not required.
#
# How to get it (free):
# 1. Go to https://www.weatherapi.com/
# 2. Sign up for a free account (no credit card needed)
# 3. Copy your API key from the dashboard
WEATHER_API_KEY=your_weatherapi_key_here
